squat
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:to settle on an area of public land before acquiring a legal right to it; to occupy Maori (or Crown) without any legal title (cf. SQUATTER n1). squatter a) History: a runholder who originally held land by squatting. b) a rich farmer; a station-owner. (absol or constr with on)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
